Her flesh flared up with pustules and power.
Training armor passed down for generations, it’s said to have been worn by a samurai during his younger years before the carnage began.
She inherited the armor of a bloodthirsty ancestor who slayed farmers and laid to waste thousands of acres of farmlands.
Its dazzling appearance contrasted with the darkness in her heart.
Armor carves its way through the soft flesh that remains, as bone-like fragments protrude in unnatural patterns.
A soaked, tattered gown wrapped in algae and dripping with murky seawater.
Everlasting frost penetrated her skin and tore apart her exposed flesh.
A torn kimono embroidered with red spider lilies.
It was capable of making durable and dangerous objects at will.
After a night of killing, she liked to walk on the beach before the sun rose.
A traditional outfit with a futuristic twist.
Awake anew in Realms beyond belief.
An eye for an eye.
Drenched and left out in the cold, your seething hate keeps you going.
A soft, spring-like appearance that deceives Survivors into dropping their guard.

Description.LocalizedString: A short, messy bob decorated with a patterned headband.

An elaborate hairstyle that is held together with pins, combs and supernatural energies.
An eerie face erupted from her flesh, revealing her birthright.
Fury rushed through her blood as she attacked. Her jet-black hair flowed wildly, the ribbon failing to keep it contained.
When she closed her eyes, she saw blood. She heard screams. And she was the one causing it. A pale spirit filled with the rage of her ancestors. And the pain.
The mask did little to obscure the fury that hid beneath the surface.
A cadaverous, ancient face, judging the world from the gloom of two empty eyes.
Oily, inky hair fused with algae.
As she drifted through glacial winds, the everlasting frost whitened and froze her disheveled hair.
A tangle of long black hair adorned with blood red flowers.
A mask they found themselves wearing at the masquerade ball.
She appeared as a versatile monster whose unique skills could cause all sorts of chaos.
Sunburns aren’t so much the problems as the sunlight is.
Her salt-and-pepper bangs stopped just above her blue eyes.
The oath you made cannot be broken.
A dramatic makeup for a tasteful revenge.
Glassy, empty eyes and blue lips: the effects of Death’s embrace.
A dramatic makeup for a tasteful revenge.
A color that pays homage to the trees that withered and the death that soon followed.
A crown emanating a festive and ominous aura created by The Entity’s biggest fan.

A crown crafted for a very special anniversary.
“Thank you for supporting & inspiring us along the years!” —The Dead by Daylight Team

Description.LocalizedString: They say this precious blade came from the sea. Forged from iron sands, this long, sharp blade was kept in the Yamaoka family for generations.

Whether the blade's edges were torn by design, or years of use, none can tell.
Her ancient blade oozed with nectar, forged by serum and steel.
A sword of jagged bamboo bunches. Once used to train, it now has a much more malicious purpose.
When she held the weapon, she felt a surge of fury, a rage she wanted to unleash.
Jagged and dull, its hideous edge took all her anger and fury to wield.
Carved from bone, the ancient blade is hued with the dying colors of twilight before the darkest night.
A sharpened whale bone encrusted with sea-washed barnacles.
Clusters of sharp ice grew over her ancestral sword, turning the weapon into a blade of ice.
An ornamental sword once used to protect the household from evil spirits.
The hardened crystals formed into a deadly weapon capable of impaling nearly anything.
She liked watching the fish swimming in the clear water and decided to take a part of them back home.
A dangerous blade made of shiny metal of unknown origin.
The blade is engraved with secrets in a language unknown to you. But if you come closer…
A legendary sword used as a tool for usurpation, howling for blood.
An ancestral blade abandoned at the bottom of a pond.
A pink-hued blade that evokes the changing of seasons and the loss it brings.
A blade crafted of bull’s horn, adorned with a dangling scarlet ribbon.
